Let \sigma \equiv 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen g\colon  B\to  A,\epsilon \colon  f\circ  g =1_{B}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 be a section of a function f\colon  A\to  B. Then the coherent remainder of \sigma  is a proposition.

fr:mainmatter.fr:tex:
  \begin {aligned}
   P &:\equiv 
   \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}

 \mathopen {}\left \lparen g
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
,\epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}

   \cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}

 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}

   \\
